Technical documentation ensures that Azure environments remain understandable, maintainable, and transferable between administrators.

Recommended documentation includes:

* Architecture diagrams
* Network topology
* Resource inventory
* Identity configuration
* Backup procedures
* Disaster recovery plans
* Operational runbooks
* Contact information

For example, documenting virtual network peering relationships helps future administrators troubleshoot connectivity issues efficiently.

A real-life use case is reducing onboarding time for new cloud engineers joining an operations team.

Comprehensive documentation improves collaboration and long-term operational stability.
